 A policeman was killed yesterday and an expatriate sustained bullet wound after suspected kidnappers abducted three Chinese nationals in Itagunmodi, Atakumosa West Local Government Area of Osun State. The area contains gold mines. The gunmen kidnapped the expatriates while they were working on the mining site located in the town. Investigation revealed that a Police Orderly was killed in the process of trying to stop the kidnappers from abducting the foreigners. The Osun State Police Public Relations Officer (PPRO), Mrs Abiodun Ige, promised that the state police command would get to the root of the matter. She further stated that, all hands would be on deck to bring the evil perpetrators to book. Meanwhile, one of the expatriates, who attempted to escape after the gunmen held them hostage, was reportedly shot and presently receiving treatment at the Obafemi Awolowo Unity (OAU) Teaching Hospital, Ile- Ife.